        {
          "type": "CommentSubheadingTitle",
          "title": "Freedom from persistent sin",
          "precomment": "",
          "refgroups": [
            {
              "type": "ReferenceGroup",
              "primaryrefs": [
                {
                  "type": "Reference",
                  "refclass": "A",
                  "comment": "John is not saying that Christians are absolutely sinless. He says elsewhere that to claim sinless perfection is to deceive oneself (1Jn 1:8). But when people are born again there is the real possibility of living lives in which sin is not the norm. As believers abide in Christ more deeply, the grip of sin upon their lives is lessened.",
                  "continuation": false,
                  "bcvreferences": [
                    "62003006-62003009"
